        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Principles of Operation</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Speed Control</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Pressing the CRUISE/RPM switch turns the speed control system on. Pressing and releasing the SET -
                switch while the vehicle is traveling at the desired speed activates the speed control system.
            </para>
            <para>Tapping the RESUME +/SET - switch while in the set mode respectively, increases or decreases the
                maintained vehicle speed by 1.6 km/h (1 mph) per tap. If the respective button is pressed and held, the
                vehicle speed continues to accelerate or decelerate until the button is released.
            </para>
            <para>Pressing the CRUISE/RPM switch, or turning the ignition switch to the OFF position, turns the speed
                control system off. Applying the brake puts the speed control system into the STANDBY mode. Pressing the
                RESUME + button, when the speed control system is in the STANDBY mode causes the vehicle to accelerate
                to the last set speed. Resume does not function if the OFF button is pressed, the ignition switch is in
                the OFF position or if the current vehicle speed is below the minimum operational speed, 48 km/h (30
                mph).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When the brake pedal is applied, an electrical signal on circuit 2233 (OR-YL) from the brake
                        switch to the ECM deactivates the system.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection and Verification</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the customer concern.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect for obvious signs of mechanical and electrical damage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If an obvious cause for an observed or reported concern is found, correct the cause (if
                    possible) before proceeding to the next step.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the speedometer operates correctly without speed control by test driving the
                    vehicle. If the speedometer does not operate correctly, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s08307_X4130029.xml" xrefid="x4130029">Instrument Cluster</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the brake lamps are operating correctly. If the brake lamps are not operating
                    correctly, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s08307_X4170126.xml" xrefid="x4170126">Exterior Lighting</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the cause is not visually evident, connect the diagnostic tool to the data link
                    connector (DLC) and carry out the diagnostic tool data link test. The ECM monitors the speed control
                    system for proper voltages and sets DTC 221 if incorrect.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pinpoint Tests</title>
            <table id="t1105052" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>PINPOINT TEST A: DTC 221 THE SPEED CONTROL IS INOPERATIVE</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A1 CHECK FOR DTCS</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Review the recorded DTCs from the engine control module (ECM) self-test.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Are any ECM DTCs recorded with DTC 221?</emph>
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Refer to EGES-305, Engine Diagnostics Manual and the ECM Diagnostic Trouble Code
                                    (DTC) Index.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A2.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A2 CHECK CIRCUIT 298 (VT/OG) AT THE CRUISE/RPM SWITCH FOR AN
                                        OPEN
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Remove the CRUISE/RPM switch and the RESUME +/SET - switch from the
                                            instrument panel. For additional information, refer to Speed Control Switch
                                            in this section.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            CRUISE/RPM Switch C2178
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between CRUISE/RPM switch C2178 pin 4, circuit 298
                                            (VT/OG), harness side and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024642.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="128px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A3.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Verify the power distribution center (PDC) fuse F46 is OK, REPAIR circuit 298
                                    (VT/OG). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A3 CHECK CIRCUIT 248 (TN-OR) AT THE RESUME +/SET - SWITCH FOR AN
                                        OPEN
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            Resume +/Set - Switch C2177
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between RESUME +/SET - switch C2177 pin D, circuit
                                            248C (TN-OR), harness side and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024643.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="128px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Go to A4.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Verify the power distribution center (PDC) fuse F46 is OK, REPAIR circuit 248
                                    (TN-OR). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A4 CHECK CIRCUIT 248 (TN/OG) FOR A SHORT TO VOLTAGE</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            ECM C175a
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between CRUISE/RPM switch C2178 pin 3, circuit 248B
                                            (TN/OG), harness side and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024644.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage less than 0.2 volt?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A5.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 248 (TN/OG). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A5 CHECK CIRCUIT 248 (TN/OG) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between ECM C175a pin 6, circuit 248 (TN/OG),
                                            harness side and CRUISE/RPM switch C2178 pin 3, circuit 248 (TN/OG), harness
                                            side.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024645.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 0.5 ohm?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A6.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 248 (TN/OG). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A6 CHECK CIRCUIT 5133 (WH) FOR A SHORT TO VOLTAGE</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                            ECM C175b
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between RESUME +/SET - switch C2177 pin B, circuit
                                            5133 (WH), harness side and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024646.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage less than 0.2 volt?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A7.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 5133 (WH). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A7 CHECK CIRCUIT 133 (BK) FOR A SHORT TO VOLTAGE</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between RESUME +/SET - switch C2177 pin H, circuit 133
                                            (BK), harness side and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024647.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage less than 0.2 volt?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A8.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 133 (BK). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A8 CHECK CIRCUIT 5133 (WH) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between RESUME +/SET - switch C2177 pin B, circuit
                                            5133 (WH), harness side and ECM C175b pin 21, circuit 5133 (WH), harness
                                            side.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024648.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 0.5 ohm?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A9.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 5133 (WH). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A9 CHECK CIRCUIT 133 (BK) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the resistance between RESUME +/SET - switch C2177 pin H, circuit
                                            133 (BK), harness side and ECM C175b pin 14, circuit 133 (BK), harness side.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024649.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 0.5 ohm?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A10.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPAIR circuit 133 (BK). CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A10 CHECK THE CRUISE/RPM SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Connect:</emph>
                                            CRUISE/RPM Switch C2178
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Measure the voltage between CRUISE/RPM switch C2178 pin 3, circuit 248B
                                            (TN/OG), back probe and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024650.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>GO to A11.</para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>REPLACE the CRUISE/RPM switch. CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">A11 CHECK THE RESUME +/SET - SWITCH</emph>
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>
                                            <emph type="bold">Connect:</emph>
                                            RESUME +/SET - Switch C2177
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>While depressing the RESUME + switch, measure the voltage between RESUME
                                            +/SET - switch C2177 pin B, circuit 5133 (WH), back probe, and ground; and
                                            while depressing the SET - switch, measure the voltage between RESUME +/SET
                                            - switch C2177 pin H, circuit 133 (BK), back probe, and ground.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024651.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Are the voltages greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new ECM. REFER to the Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual. CLEAR the
                                    DTCs. REPEAT the self-test.
                                </para>
                                <para></para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>INSTALL a new CRUISE/RPM switch or RESUME +/SET - switch. CLEAR the DTCs. REPEAT
                                    the self-test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
